ic cause. Ichthyosis caused by the same gene can vary considerably in severity and symptoms. Some ichthyoses do not appear to fit exactly into any one type. Different genes can produce ichthyoses with similar symptoms. Of note, X-linked ichthyosis is associated with [[Kallmann syndrome]] (close to the [[KAL1 gene|''KAL1'' gene]]). The most common or well-known types are:<ref>[http://www.scalyskin.org/column.cfm?ColumnID=14 Types of Ichthyosis], Foundation for Ichthyosis & Related Skin Types (F.I.R.S.T.)</ref>\n\n=== Genetic simple ichthyoses ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name\n! [[OMIM]]\n! Gene\n!Protein\n|-\n|[[Ichthyosis vulgaris]]\n|{{OMIM2|146700}}\n|''[[Filaggrin|FLG]]''\n|Filaggrin\n|-\n|[[X-linked ichthyosis]]\n|{{OMIM2|308100}}\n|''[[Steroid sulfatase|STS]]''\n|Steroid sulfatase\n|-\n| [[Nonbullous congenital ichthyosiform erythroderma|Congenital ichthyosiform erythroderma, Nonbullous]] (nbCIE)\n|{{OMIM2|242100}}\n|''[[TGM1]]'', ''[[ALOXE3]]''/''[[ALOX12B]]''\n|Transglutaminase 1<br>Arachidonate lipoxygenase 3<br>Arachidonate 12-lipoxygenase, 12R type\n|-\n|[[Epidermolytic hyperkeratosis]] (bullous ichthyosis, bCIE)\n|{{OMIM2|113800}}\n|''[[KRT1]]'', ''[[KRT10]]''\n|[[Keratin]]s\n|-\n|[[Harlequin-type ichthyosis]]\n|{{OMIM2|242500}}\n|''[[ABCA12]]''\n|ATP-binding cassette transporter 12\n|-\n|[[Ichthyosis bullosa of Siemens]]\n|{{OMIM2|146800}}\n|''[[KRT2]]''\n|Keratin 2A\n|-\n|[[Ichthyosis hystrix]], Curth-Macklin type\n|{{OMIM2|146590}}\n|''[[KRT1]]''\n|Keratin 1\n|-\n|Hystrix-like ichthyosis with deafness\n|{{OMIM2|602540}}\n|''[[GJB2]]''\n|Connexin-26 (Gap junction beta-2)\n|-\n|[[Lamellar ichthyosis]], type 1\n| {{OMIM2|242300}}\n| ''[[TGM1]]''\n| Transglutaminase 1\n|-\n| Lamellar ichthyosis, type 2\n| {{OMIM2|601277}}\n| ''[[ABCA12]]''\n| ATP-binding cassette transporter 12\n|-\n| Lamellar ichthyosis, type 3\n| {{OMIM2|604777}}\n| ''[[CYP4F22]]''\n|Cytochrome P450, subfamily 4F, polypeptide 22\n|-\n| Lamellar ichthyosis, type 4\n| {{OMIM2|613943