ring a Genius (Has a Vermeer Mystery Been Solved?) |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2013/11/vermeer-secret-tool-mirrors-lenses |website=Vanity Fair |first=Kurt |last=Andersen |date=29 November 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131130173927/http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2013/11/vermeer-secret-tool-mirrors-lenses |archivedate=30 November 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Obscura>{{cite web|title=Vermeer and the Camera Obscura |url=http://www.essentialvermeer.com/camera_obscura/co_one.html |website=Essential Vermeer 2.0 |accessdate=30 July 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140925140616/http://www.essentialvermeer.com/camera_obscura/co_three.html#.VES10MlTCSo |archivedate=25 September 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=wadum95>B. Broos, A. Blankert, J. Wadum, A. K. Wheelock Jr. (1995) ''Johannes Vermeer'', Waanders Publishers, Zwolle</ref>\n<ref name=Tims>''[[Tim's Vermeer]]'' (2013) documentary \u2013 See 40:50 onwards</ref>\n<ref name=bryson>{{cite book|last1=Bryson|first1=Bill|title=A Short History of Nearly Everything|date=2014|publisher=Lulu Press|isbn=978-1312792562|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yRuICgAAQBAJ&pg=PT442}}</ref>\n<!--\n<ref name=Dolnick>{{Cite book |name=The Forger's Spell: A True Story of Vermeer, Nazis, and the Greatest Art Hoax of the Twentieth Century |last=Dolnick |first=Edward |authorlink=Edward Dolnick |publisher=[[HarperCollins]] |year=2008 |isbn=0-06-082541-3, 9780060825416}}</ref>\n-->}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{Cite book|title=Dutch Paintings in the Metropolitan Museum of Art|last=Liedtke|first=Walter A. |authorlink=Walter Liedtke|year=2007|publisher=[[Metropolitan Museum of Art]]|isbn=978-0-300-12028-8}}\n{{Reflist|group=Liedtke|refs=\n<ref name=p866 group=Liedtke>W. Liedtke, p. 866.</ref>\n<ref name=p867 group=Liedtke>W. Liedtke, p. 867.</ref>\n<ref name=p893 group=Liedtke>W. Liedtke, p. 893.</ref>}} \n* {{Cite book|title=Vermeer and His Milieu: A Web of Social History|last=Montias